        "text": "I would like to request that this act be extended to the needless destruction of video games. Many publishers nowadays design video games to require connections to official servers, meaning that once they choose to end support, the games are functionally destroyed. I ask that publishers be required to design games with an end of life plan which allows players ways of continuing to play these games even after official support has ended. Many games already do this. Thank you for your consideration.",
